{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"36cd6874-f567-4ed9-90cb-80423a3d2c6c","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter` (before `--`) | `--filter` (after `--`) |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\nOn .NET 8 the `--` separator is required — everything after it is forwarded to the new test platform. (.NET 9+ SDK integrates natively and won't need `--`.)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"719b75aa-37fa-4396-8af5-7adbb2647948","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a codebase task. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-code-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage or you use `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` with built-in coverage\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump` and `--blame-hang` with its timeout becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nWith the new platform, `dotnet test` still works but arguments specific to Microsoft.Testing.Platform need to be passed after `--`, since the platform has its own CLI interface separate from the standard dotnet test arguments.\n\nOn .NET 8, I can either use `dotnet test` with `--` to forward arguments to the test host, or run the test executable directly. The equivalent command would pass the new flag names along with the other options like coverage and reporting formats after the `--` separator.\n\nI should note that each feature requires its corresponding NuGet package: `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for coverage reporting, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for TRX output, and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` for dump collection. The `--filter` syntax is still supported for backward compatibility.","outputTokens":1060,"requestId":"E3D9:3FC1BD:15E0B23:188140F:6A05203F"},"id":"eda7848d-ba98-419d-abcb-04f65940b3ed","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:07:29.661Z","parentId":"321c02b2-494c-4e6c-84d8-796906746db0"}
